    <h1>Multiple Integrals</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Active Calculus &middot; CC BY-SA &middot; <a href="https://activecalculus.org">activecalculus.org</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">Single integrals add up slices along a line. <strong>Double integrals</strong> add up over a region in the plane. <strong>Triple integrals</strong> add up over a volume. <strong>Change of variables</strong> (polar, cylindrical, spherical) makes hard regions easy by matching the coordinate system to the geometry.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Double integrals -->
    <h3>Double integrals</h3>
    <p>The double integral of f(x, y) over a region R gives the signed volume under the surface. Compute it as an iterated integral: integrate with respect to one variable, then the other.</p>

    <!-- SVG: Region of integration in 2D -->
    <div class="flex justify-center my-6">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 300 260" class="w-full max-w-sm" style="font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;">
        <!-- Axes -->
        <line x1="40" y1="220" x2="280" y2="220" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.3"/>
        <line x1="40" y1="220" x2="40" y2="20" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.3"/>
        <text x="285" y="225" fill="currentColor" font-size="12" fill-opacity="0.5">x</text>
        <text x="35" y="15" fill="currentColor" font-size="12" fill-opacity="0.5">y</text>
        <!-- Region R (shaded area between two curves) -->
        <path d="M 80 220 Q 120 100 180 80 Q 220 70 250 90 L 250 220 Z" fill="#a1a1aa" fill-opacity="0.15" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-opacity="0.4"/>
        <!-- Top boundary curve -->
